		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Google search shows that the Famicom microphone is a level detector that connects to bit D2 of controller 1. This bit exists only on the expansion port of a front-loader, not the controller ports on the front panel. See also <a href="http://www.nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=31913" class="postlink">previous Famicom mic discussion</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

